BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Concert featuring woodwind quintet\, Amethyst Winds
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T190000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T200000
UID:260324VvzWZFma6keUQ3UjUIbCVg
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/OASDaBHqU0-1tx67XDlNsQ.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Join us on Saturday\, March 28\, 2026\, at 7pm for a concert f
 eaturing woodwind quintet\, Amethyst Winds. The concert is free and open t
 o the public\, and an offering will be collected with 50% going to the per
 former and the other half supporting St. Mark’s Piano and Organ Fund. Th
 e concert will be followed with a festive reception in the Parlor. Everyon
 e is welcome! For more information\, please get in touch with Westley at m
 usic@stmarksevanston.org. Following the concert\, there will be a festival
  reception for all in our parlor.\n\nDetails: St. Mark’s Episcopal Churc
 h \\(1509 Ridge Ave\, Evanston\\). Parking is limited to street parking\, 
 but plenty is within walking distance. \n\nMeet the performer:\n\nAmethys
 t Winds is a woodwind quintet that calls St. Mark’s home. Members includ
 e: Lauren Moldenhauer \\(flute\\)\, Claire Bravo Cutting \\(oboe\\)\, West
 ley Art Hodges \\(clarinet\\)\, Walter van Gieson \\(bassoon\\)\, Connor C
 owart \\(french horn\\). More information about the ensemble can be found 
 on their website: www.amethystwinds.org
LOCATION:St. Mark's Church
URL:https://www.stmarksevanston.org/concerts
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sandra Hansen | Our Exquisite Pollution Series: Under the Sea
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T090000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T160000
UID:260324JYWDmy4N9kaczgEdpRorqQ
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/GIIFADiBeEG0XP67s21Odg.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:The Evanston Art Center \\(EAC\\) is excited to welcome the pu
 blic to our upcoming exhibition\,  Sandra Hansen | Our Exquisite Pollutio
 n Series: Under the Sea. The exhibition will be on display from March 28 -
  April 26\, 2026\, with an opening reception on Sunday\, March 29\, from 1
 -4pm that will be free and open to the public.\n\nIn Our Exquisite Polluti
 on Series: Under the Sea\, environmental artist Sandra Hansen creates wate
 r scenes with pure\, sustainable handmade paper and repurposed plastics fo
 und decaying on the beaches. As the environmental crisis grows larger\, so
  does Hansen’s art. She moved from oil painting to paper making and bega
 n crafting massive papers to explain the immensity of the issue. Hansen’
 s work has evolved into installation with lighting\, sound\, and movement\
 , where viewers are engulfed in an underwater-like space with paper sea cr
 eatures.
LOCATION:Evanston Art Center
URL:https://www.evanstonartcenter.org/exhibitions/sandra-hansen-our-exquis
 ite-pollution-series-under-sea
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Idle Muse Theatre Company Presents "The Three Musketeers"
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T200000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T200000
UID:260324Aowjj-yCSE64_YrmJWzoJA
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/505PC55KG0GXlUkpl7LDeg.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Idle Muse Theatre Company launches its 20th anniversary season
  with The Three Musketeers\, March 26 - April 25\, written by Robert Kauzl
 aric\, directed by Idle Muse Artistic Director Evan Jackson adapted from t
 he novel by Alexandre Dumas and originally commissioned for the 2010 Illin
 ois Shakespeare Festival\, at The Edge Off-Broadway Theater\, 1133 W Catal
 pa Ave. \n\nIdle Muse celebrates 20 years of productions with The Three M
 usketeers. Based on Alexander Dumas’s celebrated 1844 novel\, the Jeff A
 ward-winning Robert Kauzlaric adapts the French tale of swashbuckling intr
 igue\, adventure and fellowship as newly-minted musketeer D’Artagnan and
  the famous “three inseparables\,” Athos\, Porthos and Aramis take on 
 the machinations of a scheming cardinal and his minions.\n\nThe performanc
 e schedule is Thursdays\, Fridays and Saturdays at 8 p.m. and Sundays at 3
  p.m.\, with an added Wednesday performance on April 22 at 8 p.m. General 
 admission tickets are now on sale for $30 and $20 for seniors and students
  with $50 “pay it forward” tickets that assist in subsidizing tickets 
 for those who may not be able to access the production otherwise. Tickets 
 and additional group discounts are available at IdleMuse.org or the Idle M
 use Theatre Company Box Office\, 773.340.9438.
LOCATION:The Edge Off-Broadway
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=
 5#/details/idle-muse-theatre-company-presents-the-three-musketeers/1818109
 7/2026-03-28T20
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Rent
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T193000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260328T220000
UID:260319nQieOpesGEm1qb8mAGWLug
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/uCv7Ek3Hq0ueBkCvcouYNg.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Lower East Side of New York City. End of the millennium. Mark 
 and Roger are roommates\, and they can’t afford rent \\(again\\). But th
 ey don’t let that stop them from enjoying life while they can. They find
  solace in their community of fellow artists and activists who are also tr
 ying to make ends meet as they struggle through life\, love\, their art\, 
 the AIDS crisis\, and paying \\(or not paying\\) rent. Jonathan Larson’s
  final musical still resonates today about the importance of trying to get
  your voice heard\, even if it seems no one is listening.\n\nOn Sunday Mar
 ch 29\, join us for a post-show discussion with Rent dramaturgs and visit
 ors from Chicago House on the history and current state of the AIDs crisis
 \, centered around the power of community care. The discussion includes re
 sources for people currently living with HIV/AIDs.\n\nOn Friday\, April 10
 \, join us for a post-show discussion with members of the cast and artisti
 c team of Rent.
LOCATION:Newhart Family Theatre
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=
 5#/details/rent/18337008/2026-03-28T19
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
