BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Art of Dressing Salon: A Brief History of Lingerie
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260329T173000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260329T190000
UID:260325I7nVF7OvlUOT7XQS9-XKTQ
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/D3MErmJx-USGwQWneNTAgg.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:For centuries\, intimate garments and loungewear have reflecte
 d more than fashion. They tell stories about culture\, identity\, and how 
 women relate to their bodies.\n\nDuring this gathering\, Bella Otér will 
 guide guests through a brief history of lingerie and loungewear\, from the
 ir practical origins to their evolution as expressions of comfort\, confid
 ence\, and personal presence. We will also share the story of Belle Otero\
 , the Belle Époque performer whose presence and independence inspired the
  name behind Bella Otér.\n\nGuests will also experience our Bella Otér 
 Tea Bar\, where you will create your own custom tea blend using organic he
 rbs and botanicals from Sit In Savor. Inspired by apothecary style blendin
 g\, guests will craft a personalized tea designed around aroma\, flavor\, 
 and relaxation.\n\nThe evening includes\n\nA short talk on the history of 
 lingerie and loungewear\n\nThe story behind Belle Otero and Bella Otér\n\
 nA guided tea blending experience\n\nTime to explore the boutique\n\nConve
 rsation with other women in the community\n\nThese gatherings are designed
  to feel intimate and inspiring. Space is limited. Reserve your seat- http
 s://www.bellaoter.com/pages/art-of-dressing-salon
LOCATION:Bella Otér
URL:https://www.bellaoter.com/pages/art-of-dressing-salon
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Reading to Cats & Storytime
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260329T173000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260329T183000
UID:260325DydtRlKDeEySbnOACKtsdw
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/rCXoZ6Hy90e2kya6tlPmKA.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:We’ll begin with circle time as storyteller Emily Richter re
 ads Kittens First Full Moon by Kevin Henkes\, followed by open reading t
 ime where children can bring their own books and read to our cats.\n\nThis
  event is designed for children in Pre-K through 1st grade\, accompanied b
 y one parent/guardian. \n\nEvent Details: • $35 per family \\(one child
  and one adult\\). When booking\, select “1 adult.” You will be prompt
 ed to enter your child’s name at the next step.\n\nTo help keep our cats
  relaxed and happy\, we ask all participants to use indoor voices\, walkin
 g feet\, and calm hands throughout the event. We can’t wait to share th
 is special experience with you and your little reader!
LOCATION:Paws and Claws Cat Rescue
URL:http://www.pawsandclawscatrescue.org/upcoming-events
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
