BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:City Lit and Coalescence Theatre present a Developmental Workshop 
 Presentation of Rare Wolves
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260329T193000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260329T213000
UID:2603251V9mUMgMZEmbY4xY9a65Qw
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/G6fW0lksZ0CHgKGl9NtTSQ.large.png
DESCRIPTION:Gaby Labotka's new play in development\, Rare Wolves\, is an e
 vocative\, poetic play about a pack of transgender and nonbinary people de
 cried as monsters by their families or former communities. They build thei
 r own humble utopia in the woods to escape violence and persecution and to
  nourish their humanity. They find love\, acceptance\, and joy in the comm
 unity they form together\, making them powerful beyond imagination. Please
  join us in the developmental process: Each staged reading presentation wi
 ll be followed by a Talkback facilitated by Dramaturg Zach Barr\, and a li
 nk will be provided so that additional thoughts can be submitted via a Goo
 gle Form.   The entire creative team and cast are all Non-binary or Trans 
 Artists.  This event is a celebration of International Transgender Day Of 
 Visibility n March 31st Creative Team: Playwright - Gaby Labotka Co-Direct
 ors - Gaby Labotka and Brian Pastor Dramaturg - Zach Barr Stage Manager - 
 Baylee Hudson Intimacy Director - Chels Morgan Music Composition - Dee Ett
 i-Williams and Nat Puff Costume Consultant - Saawan Tiwari Artwork - J Daw
 n Co-Producers - Brian Pastor and Dawn Shandrow Cast: Rahne - Haven AJ Cra
 wley Louve - Brynley Halverson Lupe - Ricki Romano Jean - AC Rakotoniaina 
 Bleddyn - Alec Phan Rollo - Thomas Russell Stage Directions/Christine - No
 rth Rory Homewood Content Warning: Body horror\, gender dysphoria\, transp
 hobia\, homophobia\, sexual assault\, religious trauma\, medical procedure
 \, miscarriage\, mass murder/hate crimes\, self-harm\, and firearms. \\*\\
 *\\*The venue\, United Church of Rogers Park\, is ADA accessible.\\*\\*\\*
  Coalescence Theatre Project recognizes that COVID and other contagious re
 spiratory illnesses are still a problem and a disability justice issue for
  those most at risk. Because this is a high-risk time of year\, we are req
 uiring that audience members take care of themselves and each other by wea
 ring masks for the presentation. Surgical masks will be available at the d
 oor at no cost. Pay-What-You-Will
LOCATION:United Church of Rogers Park
URL:https://www.facebook.com/events/1708750207516843/
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
