BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Mysterious Stories and Indoor Campout\, Grades K-2
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260402T183000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260402T193000
UID:260319I_rQx3x0aUSBdirCldXUvQ
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/RYBRQtTgpU647I4aMVe02A.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Come to the Evanston Public Library - Robert Crown Branch to p
 onder mysterious stories\, historical happenings\, and strange phenomenon
  like black holes and the Loch Ness Monster! All this fun happens in the c
 ozy shadow of our indoor tent and campfire. \n\nKids in grades K-2\, and 
 their parent or caregiver\, are welcome to join us for our indoor campout 
 - featuring mysterious \\(but not scary!\\) stories\, invisible ink messa
 ge writing\, and s'mores! Feel free to come in your pjs and bring a stuff
 ed friend if you like!\n\nPlease register under your child's name only.
LOCATION:Robert Crown Branch Library - Multipurpose Room
URL:https://evanstonlibrary.bibliocommons.com/events/6967d1c639996c13d3d01
 15d
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Rent
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260402T193000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260402T220000
UID:2603194aMwePRpwk-JsQefVOj5Hg
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/uCv7Ek3Hq0ueBkCvcouYNg.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Lower East Side of New York City. End of the millennium. Mark 
 and Roger are roommates\, and they can’t afford rent \\(again\\). But th
 ey don’t let that stop them from enjoying life while they can. They find
  solace in their community of fellow artists and activists who are also tr
 ying to make ends meet as they struggle through life\, love\, their art\, 
 the AIDS crisis\, and paying \\(or not paying\\) rent. Jonathan Larson’s
  final musical still resonates today about the importance of trying to get
  your voice heard\, even if it seems no one is listening.\n\nOn Sunday Mar
 ch 29\, join us for a post-show discussion with Rent dramaturgs and visit
 ors from Chicago House on the history and current state of the AIDs crisis
 \, centered around the power of community care. The discussion includes re
 sources for people currently living with HIV/AIDs.\n\nOn Friday\, April 10
 \, join us for a post-show discussion with members of the cast and artisti
 c team of Rent.
LOCATION:Newhart Family Theatre
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=
 5#/details/rent/18337008/2026-04-02T19
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
