 unch Buffet on Sunday\, April 5 from 10 a.m. to 2 p.m.\, priced at $48.95
  per person and $18.95 for children under 10. Owner Amy Morton promises a 
 brunch that will “knock the whiskers off the Easter Bunny.”\n\nThe fes
 tive buffet will feature Eggs Benedict\, French Toast Casserole with custo
 mizable toppings\, whole poached salmon\, shrimp cocktail\, Chicken Piccat
 a and much more. A Donut Bar invites guests to build their own dessert cre
 ations with sundae-style toppings.\n\nLeTour will be open for brunch only 
