BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Blue Monday: Corey Dennison
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260406T200000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260406T200000
UID:260221XyASloN1hUGZWFL0b_wADw
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/zftVnFvxnUex3yfWBd20cQ.large.png
DESCRIPTION:Formed in 2013\, The Corey Dennison Band has become a favorite
  attraction at Chicago blues venues\, including twice-weekly appearances a
 t Kingston Mines. Led by Corey Dennisons soulful voice and muscular guitar
 \, the band released its self-titled studio debut for Delmark Records in 2
 016 after honing 13 original songs night after night on the bandstand. Cor
 eys decade-long stint with Carl Weathersby and Gerry Hundts tenure with Ni
 ck Moss are evident on the disc but blend effortlessly into a dynamic new 
 Chicago sound. Critics and radio polls responded glowingly as the album ga
 rnered rave reviews and worldwide airplay\, netting chart positions on the
  Roots Music and Living Blues Radio Reports. Nominations followed suit\, w
 ith a nod for Best Emerging Artist from the Blues Music Awards\, a pair fr
 om Blues Blast Magazine\, and Grammy balloting. The strength of the bands 
 repertoire is matched only by the charisma of the stage show\; its not unc
 ommon to see Corey belting out the blues\, unamplified\, in the heart of t
 he audience while the band steps in time to the groove. Its not novelty fo
 r these musicians and entertainers\, as its exactly where they want to be.
LOCATION:Evanston SPACE
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=
 5#/details/blue-monday-corey-dennison/18170642/2026-04-06T20
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:A Legacy in Miniature: Rotary's Fight to End Polio
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260406T090000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260406T170000
UID:260317nQ1tMCfK-kSlDaejBU5wKw
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/8GVvHqDMbEewojpTxLlrXA.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:A Legacy in Miniature: Rotary’s Fight to End Polio\n\nTo hon
 or Rotary’s decades-long commitment to eradicating polio\, miniature art
 ists from around the world were invited to recreate powerful moments from 
 this historic global effort. The pieces are currently on display at One Ro
 tary Center\, and the public is invited to view the art and learn more abo
 ut the fight to end polio worldwide.
LOCATION:One Rotary Center
URL:https://magazine.rotary.org/rotary/october_2025/MobilePagedArticle.act
 ion?articleId=2085663#articleId2085663
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
