UID:260324-7Ce1PBhCkmK3tvpEZBh8g
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/mqtWSFNDcUORT2XLSonkGw.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:The Book Stall is thrilled to welcome Bill Kurtis to the W
 innetka Chapel on Tuesday\, April 7 at 6:30 pm for a discussion with Pet
 er Sagal featuring his new book\, Whirlwind: My Life Reporting the News.
  Starting with his coverage of the largest tornado in Kansas history\, leg
 endary correspondent\, anchorman\, and producer Bill Kurtis details his wh
 irlwind career reporting American history as it unfolded\, from the Chicag
 o Seven to Charles Manson to Agent Orange. A fast-paced\, entertaining\, a
 nd inspiring story about the potent combination of talent and luck in the 
 network era of television.\n\nThe ticket price is $41 and includes a copy 
 of the book. Mr. Kurtis will be happy to sign his work!
LOCATION:The Winnetka Chapel
URL:https://thebookstall.com/event/2026-04-07/whirlwind-evening-bill-kurti
 s-and-peter-sagal
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
