BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:"Donovan's Garage" jazz presents--"In the Lab" with Frank Russell
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260414T190000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260414T203000
UID:26032503FPL8X5VkaKUnjCT7EiyA
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/nVej7BVaKkSe7ToVSPdVEw.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Evanston Jazz:  “Donovan’s Garage” jazz brings all-star
  quintet of Chicago jazzmen to Evanston on April 10\n\nHeadlining is the a
 cclaimed Chicago Jazz bass player Frank Russell\, the official bassist for
  the legendary South African group Ladysmith Black Mambazo.  Frank is cur
 rently recording an album featuring Ladysmith and many of Chicago’s fine
 st jazz musicians including Robert Irving III\, Howard Levy\, Bobby Broom\
 , Jahari Stampley\, Corey Wilkes and more.  \\(You might recognize a few 
 of those names from earlier “Donovan’s Garage” shows.\\)\n\nThis is 
 a “Donovan’s Garage jazz event that you don’t want to miss.  Go to 
 www.donovanmxon.com to read about each of the players.\n\nDonovan is label
 ing this show “In the ‘Lab’ with Frank Russell\,” a nod to the way
  these shows bring the audience into the process of jazz.  It will be Tue
 sday\, April 10 at the AKAR Auditorium\, 2715 Hurd Ave. in Evanston. \\(Ac
 ross the street from Willard School.\\)  As with all “Donovan’s Garag
 e” jazz events\, the show is free and families are welcome.  Doors open
  at 6 for an exhibit of the work of Evanston artist Angela Williams.  The
  music starts at 7.\n\nThis is going to be an amazing show. Here is a bit 
 about each of that players who will round out this quintet of Chicago jazz
  artists.\n\nTim McNamara on sax and flute: He’s performed with jazz lum
 inaries such as Benny Carter\, Roy Hargrove\, Branford Marsalis\, Doc Seve
 rinsen and Clark Terry.  Tim has toured with major pop\, R&B\, and Broadw
 ay productions and leads the jazz group Level 4.\n\nKevin O’Connell on p
 iano: He’s recorded with Clifford Jordan and Vernel Fournier\, performin
 g with Philly Joe Jones\, Billy Hart\, Cab Calloway and many other jazz gi
 ants.  In Chicago since 1993 he’s played all the local jazz clubs like 
 the Jazz Showcase and the Green Mill.  Now he’s adding “Donovan’s G
 arage” to the list.\n\nTyrone Blair on drums: Tyrone has toured internat
 ionally and across the United States with numerous jazz\, gospel\, and con
 temporary artists. He has contributed to recordings\, film and television 
 soundtracks\, and major concert performances including the Chicago Jazz Fe
 stival.\n\nDonovan Mixon on jazz guitar: Donovan lives in Evanston and is 
 well-known in the Chicago jazz scene.  He’s just released a new album 
 “Finding Center.” Donovan is the Founder of the “Donovan’s Garage 
 “ jazz events\, dedicated to bringing great Chicago jazz to Evanston.\n\
 n\\(If you wonder what “Donovan’s Garage” jazz is all about\, here
 ’s a bit of backstory.  Donovan is on a mission to bring great Chicago 
 jazz to Evanston. Over the past three years\, more than 80 of Chicago’s 
 finest jazz players have accepted his invitation to come to Evanston for t
 hese free performances at the AKAR. The gift of these free shows to Evans
 ton is why Donovan was awarded the 2025 Mayor’s Award for the Arts in Ev
 anston.\\)\n\nRead more about the players and sign up for Donovan’s news
 letter at www.donovanmixon.com.
LOCATION:AKAR Auditorium
URL:http://donovanmixon.com
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
