DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260416T190000
UID:260325TVViElT4G065PI29xUY4wA
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/0cbb91a7-58bf-4295-bea4-df768273f0b7.large.png
DESCRIPTION:Families with children currently in middle school—or prepari
 ng to enter the middle school years—often carry questions about social d
 ynamics\, emotional well-being\, and how best to support their child’s g
 rowth. Join Cynthia Eudy\, LCSW\, Baker School Social Worker and adolesce
 nt therapist\, for a supportive parent conversation focused on practical t
 ools and strategies to help families navigate this stage with greater clar
 ity and confidence.\n\nWhen you RSVP\, you will have the opportunity to su
 bmit your questions in advance\, and Cynthia will address them during the 
 session.\n\nThursday\, April 16\n\n6:00–7:00 PM\n\nBaker Demonstration S
 chool\n\n201 Sheridan Road\, Wilmette\n\nSpace is limited.
