DESCRIPTION:The Woman’s Club of Evanston is excited to host a special bo
 ok event open to the public on Sunday\, April 19 from 1-3 PM when USA Toda
 y bestselling author Renee Rosen talks about Marshall Field and Chicago’
 s Gilded Age in her book\, What The Lady Wants.\n\nStep back in time and l
 earn the fascinating story behind the founding of Marshall Field’s durin
 g this illuminating book presentation by acclaimed historical fiction auth
 or Renee Rosen. Through her engaging storytelling\, you’ll be transporte
 d back to the elegance\, ambition\, and drama of Chicago’s Gilded Age.\n
 \nEnjoy light fare and book presentation and signing by the author. Tour t
 he historic Woman’s Clubhouse after the talk. All are welcome.\n\nTicket
 s are $25. Net proceeds from this event will support the Woman’s Club of
  Evanston Community Grants Fund.\n\nDon’t miss this wonderful afternoon 
 of history\, books\, and community!\n\nRenee Rosen lives in Chicago. Her o
 ther novels include Fifth Avenue Glamour Girl\, The Social Graces\, Park A
 venue Summer\, Windy City Blues\, White Collar Girl\, What the Lady Wants\
 , Dollface\, and her most recent Call Her Barbie.
