BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sandra Hansen | Our Exquisite Pollution Series: Under the Sea
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260422T090000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260422T160000
UID:260324C0u01oV3hUu8oS826JUmlA
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/GIIFADiBeEG0XP67s21Odg.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:The Evanston Art Center \\(EAC\\) is excited to welcome the pu
 blic to our upcoming exhibition\,  Sandra Hansen | Our Exquisite Pollutio
 n Series: Under the Sea. The exhibition will be on display from March 28 -
  April 26\, 2026\, with an opening reception on Sunday\, March 29\, from 1
 -4pm that will be free and open to the public.\n\nIn Our Exquisite Polluti
 on Series: Under the Sea\, environmental artist Sandra Hansen creates wate
 r scenes with pure\, sustainable handmade paper and repurposed plastics fo
 und decaying on the beaches. As the environmental crisis grows larger\, so
  does Hansen’s art. She moved from oil painting to paper making and bega
 n crafting massive papers to explain the immensity of the issue. Hansen’
 s work has evolved into installation with lighting\, sound\, and movement\
 , where viewers are engulfed in an underwater-like space with paper sea cr
 eatures.
LOCATION:Evanston Art Center
URL:https://www.evanstonartcenter.org/exhibitions/sandra-hansen-our-exquis
 ite-pollution-series-under-sea
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:40 Hour Domestic Violence Training
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260422T100000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260422T150000
UID:260317sC9jO3JIxUmhZGUWIwrRyA
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/-CjdixfCKk-dW5UT2pUAsw.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:YWCA Evanston/North Shore is an approved ICDVP training site f
 or the 40-hour domestic violence training\, which provides a solid base of
  knowledge for anyone working with individuals affected by domestic violen
 ce. The training covers all ICDVP required topics using a trauma-informed 
 lens\, including:\n\nDynamics of Domestic Violence\n\nEmpowerment Counseli
 ng\n\nCriminal and Civil Legal Issues\n\nSafety Planning\n\nRisk Assessmen
 t\n\nConfidentiality\n\nTeen Dating Violence\n\nImpact of Domestic Violenc
 e on Children\n\nIntroduction to Partner Abuse Intervention Strategies\n\n
 Connection to Mental Health and Substance Abuse\n\nDynamics within LGBTQ C
 ommunities\n\nElder Abuse\n\nSupporting People with Disabilities\n\nSelf a
 nd Community Care\n\nOur trainers all have years of experience\, both as e
 ducators and as service providers. Where beneficial\, we bring in guest tr
 ainers with more in-depth knowledge on specific topics. Click here to le
 arn more about how the training is conducted.\n\nDATE/TIME: April 20th\, 
 2026 - May 1st\, 2026 \\(M-F\\) from 10am -3pm CST\n\n\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\n\nQ
 UESTIONS…? CONTACT:\n\nHannah Gunter\, Senior Manager of Prevention Serv
 ices\n\nhgunter@ywca-ens.org\n\n847-864-8445 ext. 1128.
LOCATION:YWCA Evanston/North Shore
URL:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/40-hour-domestic-violence-training-ticket
 s-1980714494372?aff=oddtdtcreator
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
