BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Book Stall and ValsList JLF Present an Evening with Gaelynn Le
 a
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260423T190000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260423T200000
UID:260325ZyvsqVoP8UyCxZwyy3H8gA
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/cegZ02mNAkmqAOaJwNBrIw.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:**The Book Stall** in partnership with **Valslist Just Liste
 n Foundation** is pleased to present an evening of discussion and music wi
 th **Gaelynn Lea**\, author of the new book\, ***It Wasn't Meant to Be P
 erfect***. Folk musician\, Broadway composer\, and disability advocate Gae
 lynn Lea's warm\, funny\, poignant memoir is a love letter to every kind o
 f body\, to music\, and to making it work––inviting us to embrace all 
 of life's experiences with heart and determination. Ms. Lea will be in-con
 versation with author **Leigh Stein**. Following the talk\, Gaelynn will 
 perform a few songs for the audience!\n\n***There are two ticket options: 
 a ticket without a book ($25)\, and a ticket that includes a copy of the b
 ook ($41).*** \n\n**Gaelynn Lea** is a composer\, musician\, and disabili
 ty rights advocate. The winner of NPR Music’s Tiny Desk Contest in 2016\
 , Lea has collaborated with Michael Stipe\, The Decemberists\, and Wilco. 
 In 2022\, she composed an original score for *Macbeth* on Broadway\, sta
 rring Daniel Craig and Ruth Negga\, and later released the album *Music F
 rom Macbeth.* Lea is a sought-after public speaker about disability cultur
 e\, inclusion\, and accessibility in the arts. She was awarded a Disabilit
 y Futures Fellowship in 2024.\n\n**Leigh Stein** is the author of six book
 s\, including the national bestseller *If You’re Seeing This\, It’s M
 eant For You* and the critically acclaimed satirical novel *Self Care.* 
 She is also the creator of the Attention Economy newsletter on Substack.\n
 \n**Valslist** is a music discovery platform launched by Val Haller in 200
 7 that helps busy adults stay connected to new music through curated playl
 ists\, intimate concert experiences\, and the nationally recognized Winnet
 ka Music Festival. The newly launched Just Listen Foundation supports tour
 ing artists and engaged audiences who want to just listen.
LOCATION:The Winnetka Chapel
URL:https://thebookstall.com/event/2026-04-23/book-stall-and-valslist-jlf-
 present-evening-gaelynn-lea
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Joan Ruppert | Making the Cut
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260423T090000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260423T160000
UID:260324o3t_ESSQ1UWKtETe-17HPg
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/OY2WVMOEO0q51qe0_Ksm8A.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:The Evanston Art Center \\(EAC\\) is excited to welcome the pu
 blic to our upcoming exhibition\, Joan Ruppert | Making the Cut. The exhib
 ition will be on display from March 28 - April 26\, 2026\, with an opening
  reception on Sunday\, March 29\, from 1–4pm that will be free and open 
 to the public.\n\nJoan Tortorici Ruppert is a television producer and medi
 a content creator based in Glenview\, IL. Her exhibition Making the Cut sh
 owcases live-action collages that combine characters from her late father
 ’s vintage negatives together with contemporary environments. Each new c
 ollage is organic\, unpredictable\, and unrepeatable\, disrupting time and
  space to write new chapters in her family’s story.
LOCATION:Evanston Art Center
URL:https://www.evanstonartcenter.org/exhibitions/joan-ruppert-making-cut
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Idle Muse Theatre Company Presents "The Three Musketeers"
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260423T200000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260423T200000
UID:260324mnJvXytN30K2X13-4F4pzQ
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/505PC55KG0GXlUkpl7LDeg.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Idle Muse Theatre Company launches its 20th anniversary season
  with The Three Musketeers\, March 26 - April 25\, written by Robert Kauzl
 aric\, directed by Idle Muse Artistic Director Evan Jackson adapted from t
 he novel by Alexandre Dumas and originally commissioned for the 2010 Illin
 ois Shakespeare Festival\, at The Edge Off-Broadway Theater\, 1133 W Catal
 pa Ave. \n\nIdle Muse celebrates 20 years of productions with The Three M
 usketeers. Based on Alexander Dumas’s celebrated 1844 novel\, the Jeff A
 ward-winning Robert Kauzlaric adapts the French tale of swashbuckling intr
 igue\, adventure and fellowship as newly-minted musketeer D’Artagnan and
  the famous “three inseparables\,” Athos\, Porthos and Aramis take on 
 the machinations of a scheming cardinal and his minions.\n\nThe performanc
 e schedule is Thursdays\, Fridays and Saturdays at 8 p.m. and Sundays at 3
  p.m.\, with an added Wednesday performance on April 22 at 8 p.m. General 
 admission tickets are now on sale for $30 and $20 for seniors and students
  with $50 “pay it forward” tickets that assist in subsidizing tickets 
 for those who may not be able to access the production otherwise. Tickets 
 and additional group discounts are available at IdleMuse.org or the Idle M
 use Theatre Company Box Office\, 773.340.9438.
LOCATION:The Edge Off-Broadway
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=
 5#/details/idle-muse-theatre-company-presents-the-three-musketeers/1818109
 7/2026-04-23T20
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Sandra Hansen | Our Exquisite Pollution Series: Under the Sea
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260423T090000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260423T160000
UID:260324GjBkYNRrp0uHDS8CzlesyQ
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/GIIFADiBeEG0XP67s21Odg.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:The Evanston Art Center \\(EAC\\) is excited to welcome the pu
 blic to our upcoming exhibition\,  Sandra Hansen | Our Exquisite Pollutio
 n Series: Under the Sea. The exhibition will be on display from March 28 -
  April 26\, 2026\, with an opening reception on Sunday\, March 29\, from 1
 -4pm that will be free and open to the public.\n\nIn Our Exquisite Polluti
 on Series: Under the Sea\, environmental artist Sandra Hansen creates wate
 r scenes with pure\, sustainable handmade paper and repurposed plastics fo
 und decaying on the beaches. As the environmental crisis grows larger\, so
  does Hansen’s art. She moved from oil painting to paper making and bega
 n crafting massive papers to explain the immensity of the issue. Hansen’
 s work has evolved into installation with lighting\, sound\, and movement\
 , where viewers are engulfed in an underwater-like space with paper sea cr
