UID:2603126DCUmuRUaEeKKyysXnFSbg
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/UXW685COiEKKXgTOqNmctw.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Healthy Kids Day® is a free\, high-energy\, screen-free celeb
 ration of movement\, wellness\, and family fun! Come ready to play\, explo
 re\, and connect with YMCA staff and community partners who bring the exci
 tement — and the resources. Plus\, you’ll have a chance to win prizes\
 , including a YMCA Family Membership!\n\nBounce. Move. Create. Learn. Repe
 at.\n\nEach activity zone is thoughtfully designed for easy flow and nonst
 op fun\, so kids and families can jump right in and stay moving.\n\nDance 
 Party | Food Trucks | Prizes\n\nDate: Saturday\, April 25\, 2026\n\nTime: 
 10:00 AM -2:00 PM\n\nLocation: McGaw YMCA Sebring-Lewis Center \\(Use Entr
 ance 2 in the West Alley\\)\n\nParking: Free parking in YMCA lots\; free t
 wo-hour street parking as posted on signs\n\nFree & Open to the Public! Re
 gistration is requested in advance or sign in at the door.\n\nHealthy Kids
  Day® is also part of Downtown Evanston's Refresh & Renew Wellness Open H
 ouse. Stop by the Y\, then explore downtown fitness and wellness businesse
 s!\n\nSponsorship Opportunities\n\nReach local families and show your comm
 itment to community wellness by supporting this free family event.\n\nSpon
 sorships are available at $2\,000\, $1\,000\, and $750 levels\, each with 
 corresponding benefits. Local businesses may also reserve tabling space fo
 r $150. Due to limited space\, priority is given to small\, locally-owned 
 businesses who directly serve kids and families. Visit our website for mor
 e details: https://www.mcgawymca.org/hkd/.
LOCATION:McGaw YMCA
URL:https://www.mcgawymca.org/hkd/
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Little Dancer: A Reimagining Of Le Petit Prince
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260425T153000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260425T163000
UID:260309FUVYG50pGkWIlHAddjWwnQ
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/snMzWdGD_EK_5mGlNRKjLA.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Ede2 celebrates its 15th Anniversary with an original dance pr
 oduction “The Little Dancer: A Reimagining of Le Petit Prince” writt
 en by Antoine de Saint-Exupéry. The out-of-this-world production will fol
 low the story of a pilot marooned in the desert where they meet the myster
 ious stranger who traveled to Earth from a far away asteroid in search of 
 the meaning of connection and friendship. This family-friendly show featur
 es an eccentric cast of characters who populate various planets\, such as 
 space royalty\, a talking rose and a friendly fox\, who all teach The Litt
 le Dancer unique lessons on becoming a good person and how to care for oth
 ers. For ede2’s celebratory anniversary season\, the production will fea
 ture original music composed by Chicago Recording Academy Governor Tim Cor
 pus\, costume design by Josephine Everett\, Scenic Design by Daphne Agosin
  and Charlie Malave\, narration by Kelsey Cally and a lineup of profession
 al choreographers such as GREYSCALE Artistic Director Jessica Kondrath and
  Jus.Be House Collective’s co-founder Jordan Ordonez.
LOCATION:Studio5
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=
 5#/details/the-little-dancer-a-reimagining-of-le-petit-prince/18287332/202
 6-04-25T15
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
