BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Todd Kessler: Album Release w. Pat McKillen
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260427T193000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260427T193000
UID:260221jKcRh7X06USo8cOSlKS8Nw
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/1lKA82NzdUuB-tFihYdfkQ.large.png
DESCRIPTION:Todd Kessler is back after seven years with a brand new album 
 and a story to tell. His 2017 album About Memory served as a return to his
  singer-songwriter roots after a momentous few years following his stint o
 n NBCs The Voice\, a time spent touring both solo and with his band while 
 achieving success writing for TV and commercials. His new album\, Here Is 
 All We Have\, was forged in the solitude of lockdown and lays bare the sou
 l\, grappling with identity\, mortality\, and the relentless pursuit of me
 aning. Seeking a sonic pilgrimage\, he journeyed to Ireland\, the wellspri
 ng of his musical inspiration. Under the spellbinding direction of produce
 r Hally\, and anchored by the rhythmic alchemy of Robbie Malone \\(David G
 ray\\) and Graham Hopkins \\(Glen Hansard\\)\, Kessler conjured a collecti
 on of songs that are both intimate and expansive. The album pulses with ra
 w honesty\, where Kesslers arresting vocals intertwine with organic\, evoc
 ative arrangements\, creating a soundscape that is both timeless and deepl
 y personal.
LOCATION:Evanston SPACE
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=
 5#/details/todd-kessler-album-release-w-pat-mckillen/18170688/2026-04-27T1
 9
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Vivian's Decision: A Discussion with Della Leavitt & Lindsay Hunte
 r
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260427T180000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260427T190000
UID:260326-yOFsPVxlki8VBSFc7UnQg
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/mS5CB75KgEey7ZG7S2ZgFQ.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:The Book Stall welcomes Della Leavitt to the store for a dis
 cussion featuring her new book\, Vivian's Decision. An evocative work of 
 historical fiction\, Vivian’s Decision is an all too relevant story of
  repeated history\, female friendship\, and the strength that it takes to 
 make choices of one’s own. Ms. Leavitt will be in-conversation with auth
 or Lindsay Hunter.\n\nDella Leavitt draws inspiration from the lives of 
 resilient women. After careers in technology and math education\, she emba
 rked on an intensive study to write fiction within Chicago’s vibrant wri
 ting community. Della earned a historical novel fellowship from the Newber
 ry Library and a grant from Chicago’s Department of Cultural Affairs & S
 pecial Events \\(DCASE\\) while writing this novel. She lives in Chicago w
 ith her family.\n\nLindsay Hunter received her MFA in Writing from the Sc
 hool of the Art Institute of Chicago. Her first book\, Daddy’s\, is a 
 collection of flash fiction. Her second collection\, Don't Kiss Me\, was 
 named one of Amazon’s 10 Best Books of the Year: Short Stories. Her fi
 rst novel\, Ugly Girls\, was called by The Huffington Post “a story 
 that hits a note that’s been missing from the chorus of existing femin
 ist literature.” Her latest novel\, Eat Only When You’re Hungry\, wa
 s a Book of the Month Club selection\, a finalist for the 2017 Chicago Re
 view of Books Fiction Award\, and a 2017 NPR Great Read. She produces a
 nd hosts the podcast I’m a Writer But\, a series about writers with kids
 \, jobs\, and/or lives\, and how they make it all work \\(or don’t\\). L
 indsay’s fifth book\, a novel titled Hot Springs Drive\, is out now and
  was named one of the 12 Best Thrillers of the Year by the Washington Pos
 t. She lives in Chicago with her family.
LOCATION:The Book Stall
URL:https://thebookstall.com/event/2026-04-27/vivians-decision-discussion-
 della-leavitt-lindsay-hunter
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
