DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260428T193000
UID:260221FskeZkOdGkKhVszyZBN98A
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/Rb2t9ChjgE2txKyRpQCWhQ.large.png
DESCRIPTION:This year\, we celebrate the twentieth anniversary of Amy Wine
 houses deeply confessional second and final studio album\, Back to Black. 
 Were still as moved by the albums beauty and power in 2026 as we were in 2
 006. Rachel Drew will be backed by John Szymanski\, Michael Krayniak\, Jas
 on Batchko\, Kenn Goodman\, and Total Pro Horns \\(Max Crawford\, Paul Von
  Mertens\, and David E Smith\\). They will cover all of Back to Black\, al
 ong with selections from her album Frank and choice bootlegs and live show
 s. Rachel Drew is known for her soulful voice and self-penned tunes that b
 lend pop\, rock\, folk\, and retro soul. Her latest album\, Old Sky New\, 
 was recognized as one of the 13 Best Chicago Albums of 2024 by the Chicago
  Sun-Times and WBEZ / Vocalo-NPR.
LOCATION:Evanston SPACE
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=
 5#/details/a-tribute-to-amy-winehouse-by-rachel-drew/18170689/2026-04-28T1
 9
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Endless Game: J.D. Amato In-Conversation with Betsy Bird
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260428T183000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260428T193000
UID:260326A0QQooDzskWN_h5iR8zsfA
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/-eGArhw6_0Cd-nxlfaWGeg.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:The Book Stall is excited to welcome J.D. Amato to the store
  for a discussion with Betsy Bird featuring his new book\, The Endless G
 ame. Best known for his work in comedy television\, J.D. Amato's middle-gr
 ade graphic novel debut is an adventurous slice-of-life book about a middl
 e school boy who gets drawn into his new town’s intense summer game of c
 apture the flag\, perfect for fans of The Cardboard Kingdom and Craig of 
 the Creek.\n\nJ.D. Amato is a writer based in Astoria\, NY. He is best kn
 own for his work as a showrunner for comedy television shows like After Mi
 dnight\; Desus & Mero\; My Brother\, My Brother and Me and The Chris G
 ethard Show. He is currently an executive producer on The Undercovers\, h
 osted by Eli Manning. Beyond television and film\, J.D. has been a house p
 erformer at the Upright Citizen’s Brigade Theater\, consulted for variou
 s magicians\, performed as a mime\, and once hosted a podcast where every 
 episode was twelve hours long. He grew up on the North Shore of Chicago\, 
 and outside of writing he is an amateur distance runner and loves colorful
  things. \n\nOur conversation partner Betsy Bird is an author\, librari
 an\, reviewer of children’s literature\, public speaker\, and podcaster 
 \\(not necessarily in that order\\). She is the author of numerous picture
  books\, two books for kids ages 9–12\, two books for adults about child
 ren’s books\, and more. She currently resides in Evanston with her two k
 ids\, husband\, and cats Izzy and Hilo \\(named after the graphic novel se
 ries by Judd Winick\\).
LOCATION:The Book Stall
URL:https://thebookstall.com/event/2026-04-28/endless-game-jd-amato-conver
 sation-betsy-bird
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:40 Hour Domestic Violence Training
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260428T100000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260428T150000
UID:260317zdqUtBZ8lk2OtkiCtQoiVw
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/-CjdixfCKk-dW5UT2pUAsw.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:YWCA Evanston/North Shore is an approved ICDVP training site f
 or the 40-hour domestic violence training\, which provides a solid base of
  knowledge for anyone working with individuals affected by domestic violen
 ce. The training covers all ICDVP required topics using a trauma-informed 
 lens\, including:\n\nDynamics of Domestic Violence\n\nEmpowerment Counseli
 ng\n\nCriminal and Civil Legal Issues\n\nSafety Planning\n\nRisk Assessmen
 t\n\nConfidentiality\n\nTeen Dating Violence\n\nImpact of Domestic Violenc
 e on Children\n\nIntroduction to Partner Abuse Intervention Strategies\n\n
 Connection to Mental Health and Substance Abuse\n\nDynamics within LGBTQ C
 ommunities\n\nElder Abuse\n\nSupporting People with Disabilities\n\nSelf a
 nd Community Care\n\nOur trainers all have years of experience\, both as e
 ducators and as service providers. Where beneficial\, we bring in guest tr
 ainers with more in-depth knowledge on specific topics. Click here to le
 arn more about how the training is conducted.\n\nDATE/TIME: April 20th\, 
 2026 - May 1st\, 2026 \\(M-F\\) from 10am -3pm CST\n\n\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\n\nQ
 UESTIONS…? CONTACT:\n\nHannah Gunter\, Senior Manager of Prevention Serv
 ices\n\nhgunter@ywca-ens.org\n\n847-864-8445 ext. 1128.
LOCATION:YWCA Evanston/North Shore
URL:https://www.eventbrite.com/e/40-hour-domestic-violence-training-ticket
 s-1980714494372?aff=oddtdtcreator
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
