BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Hannibal Buress
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260429T193000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260429T193000
UID:260325rwqgk0DzXECwbgRv52oe_Q
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/MR9VH9wBiUmZ4vvtGz0A4A.large.png
DESCRIPTION:From within the bustling heart of the Windy City\, a comedian 
 named Hannibal Buress embarked upon his journey. The year was 2002\, the l
 ocation\, the Big Muddy Room at Southern Illinois University. Guided by th
 e wisdom of his friend Chidi and sharpened in the fires of Tony Trimm's "S
 unday School sessions\," young Buress was prepared to take the comedy worl
 d by storm. In 2022\, he underwent a transformation\, shedding his skin to
  become Eshu Tune in the world of music. His rhythmic anthems like "Veneer
 s remix" with Danny Brown and Paul Wall\, the lively bowling song "1-3 Poc
 ket\," and the meticulously crafted "I Lift Weights" echo through the stre
 ets. This endeavor was made possible through collaborations with creative 
 minds like Kiefer\, Tru\, Eshu Tune\, Wahsabi Papi\, Kenny Segal\, Eryn Al
 len Kane\, and Haile Supreme. Through these transformations\, Hannibal Bur
 ess remains a true warrior in the world of entertainment.
LOCATION:Northlight Theatre
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=
 5#/details/hannibal-buress/18176652/2026-04-29T19
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Flat Five
