BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:ABLEfest - celebrating 10 years of Artists Breaking Limits & Expec
 tations
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260501T190000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260501T203000
UID:260319x6508F13vUmyCZVTvfsitg
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/XWyv5g8Wdk2JpiF-Gr_BAg.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:This spring\, Chicago nonprofit A.B.L.E - Artists Breaking Lim
 its & Expectations - will mark their 10th anniversary of creating theatre 
 and film projects for\, with\, and by individuals with intellectual and de
 velopmental disabilities and other developmental disabilities. They are ce
 lebrating with a weekend-long festival April 30-May 3rd at The Edge Theate
 r in Chicago. \n\nThe festival will feature 78 performers - including 40 
 actors with intellectual and developmental disabilities - in 5 performance
 s\, including showcases and a limited run of an original full-length show.
  \n\nPerformances: \n\nThursday April 30th at 7pm - Movement Ensemble Sh
 owcase \\(ASL interpreted\\)\n\nFriday\, May 1st at 7:00 pm - The Time Cap
 sule\n\nSaturday\, May 2nd at 2:00pm - Devising Ensemble Showcase \\(ASL i
 nterpreted\\)\n\nSaturday May 2nd at 7pm - The Time Capsule \\(ASL interpr
 eted\\)\n\nSunday\, May 3rd at 2:30pm \\(audio described performance\\)\n\
 nTickets: \n\nPay-what-you-can general admission ranging from $15-$45\n\n
