BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Artemis Singers presents "Power in Harmony" Concert May 2
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260502T190000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260502T210000
UID:260324kDHn52SJt0K9_81ExNRvmQ
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/zwspcyHU3U6BPRrFmfYyhA.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Artemis Singers\, www.artemissingers.org\, Chicago’s Lesbia
 n Feminist Chorus\, will present its spring concert\, “Power in Harmony.
 " Songs on the program include “Lesbian Feminist Boogie” by Allison Do
 wning\, Chicago resident and Artemis member\; “Night” by Florence Pric
 e\, the first African-American woman to have a composition played by a maj
 or orchestra \\(Chicago Symphony Orchestra in 1933\\)\; and “Sparrow” 
 by Katie Gavin\, originally from Winnetka\, Ill.\, and arranged by Artemis
 ’s own Ab Lag. Artemis will present the Chicago premiere of “The Song 
 My Paddle Sings” by Danielle Olana Jagelski. The piece reflects the har
 mony between nature and oneself. The program features bold\, evolving harm
 onies that reflect both the music and the resilient lesbian community that
  inspires it.\n\n“Power in Harmony” is a preview of the nonprofit Arte
 mis Singers’ performance at the 14th annual Sister Singers Network \\(SS
 N\\) Choral Festival\, July 8 - 12\, in Chicago\, featuring 20 feminist ch
 oruses from around the U.S. The 60-member Artemis Singers is hosting the 2
 026 festival.
LOCATION:First Congregational Church of Evanston
URL:http://www.artemissingers.org
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
