BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:ABLEfest - celebrating 10 years of Artists Breaking Limits & Expec
 tations
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260502T140000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260502T143000
UID:260319do1cN3hJe0S5eGNgNR0lng
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/XWyv5g8Wdk2JpiF-Gr_BAg.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:This spring\, Chicago nonprofit A.B.L.E - Artists Breaking Lim
 its & Expectations - will mark their 10th anniversary of creating theatre 
 and film projects for\, with\, and by individuals with intellectual and de
 velopmental disabilities and other developmental disabilities. They are ce
 lebrating with a weekend-long festival April 30-May 3rd at The Edge Theate
 r in Chicago. \n\nThe festival will feature 78 performers - including 40 
 actors with intellectual and developmental disabilities - in 5 performance
 s\, including showcases and a limited run of an original full-length show.
  \n\nPerformances: \n\nThursday April 30th at 7pm - Movement Ensemble Sh
 owcase \\(ASL interpreted\\)\n\nFriday\, May 1st at 7:00 pm - The Time Cap
 sule\n\nSaturday\, May 2nd at 2:00pm - Devising Ensemble Showcase \\(ASL i
 nterpreted\\)\n\nSaturday May 2nd at 7pm - The Time Capsule \\(ASL interpr
 eted\\)\n\nSunday\, May 3rd at 2:30pm \\(audio described performance\\)\n\
 nTickets: \n\nPay-what-you-can general admission ranging from $15-$45\n\n
 Accessibility at all performances:\n\nAll performances are open captioned\
 n\nAll performances are relaxed - you can leave the theatre at any time if
  you need a break and sensory support tools will be available\n\nWheelchai
 r Access\n\nMasks are required for all attendees out of consideration for 
 our immunocompromised community members\n\nCast & Crew\n\nTeaching Artists
 : Braden Cleary\, Ruby Gibson\, Maddy Grady\, Kiaran Hartnett\, Kaylie Hon
 kala\, Lawrence Kern\, and Katie Yohe\n\nActors: Colleen Altman\, Colin Ba
 ar\, Marissa Bloodgood\, Christian Boyd\, Sophianna Bressette\, Rachel Buc
 hanan\, Jack Butler\, Benjamin Collins\, Sophie Earvolino\, Gabe Felshman\
 , Samuel Floersheimer\,  Ryan Foley\, Sean Grynberg\, Peter Grzeslo\, Eri
 n Harvey\, Natalia Janik\, Jonathan Jennings\, Fletcher Jones\, Xavier Jun
 iel\, Andrew Kosnik\, Emily Kwidzinski\, Matthew LaChapelle\, Emily Lavin\
 , Maggie Leal\, Lily Lundin\, Anna Luzadder\, Maggie Marren\, Matthew Marr
 en\, Carlos Mejia\, Jr\, Lucas Miezal\, John Miksis\, Claire O’Leary\, K
 ira Perdue\, Sam Radinsky\, Dorsey Schroeck\, Tommy Shimoda\, Kevin Smith\
 , Kimmy Smith\, Jake Solworth\, Zachary Wandel \n\nFacilitators: Nette An
 gelini\, Amy Bahr\, Andrea Bazzoli\, Lewis Beaver\, Lauren Berquist\, Alex
 andria Bressette\, Claire Buckley\, Julia Clavadetscher\, Margo DePorter\,
  Shannon Diegel\, Mike Falevits\, Sarah Haley\, Paige Henderson\, Ashlyn H
 orein\, Chelsea Hosler\, Avery Lareau\, Kate McDuffie\, Kaitlynn Milvert\,
  Steve O’Connell\, Erik Prather\, Carly Sells\, Julianne Shea\, Margaret
  Sheils\, Susan Sjodin\, Lindsay Stock\, Kate Vargulich\, Julia Waits\, Co
 nnor Wiles\, and Polly Yukevich\n\nCompany Manager: Haley Schroeck\n\nLigh
 ting Designer: Lea Davis\n\nDirector of ASL: Peter Wujcik\n\nASL Interpret
 ers: Sabrina Cienfuegos and Mark Motyka\n\nAudio Description: Jason Harrin
 gton\n\nKey Art Photographer: Justin Barbin\n\nA.B.L.E.’s 2025-2026 Seas
 on is partially supported by The Andrew E. Barrer Trust on behalf of the C
 hicago Lighthouse\, The Chicago Community Trust\, The Chicago Department o
 f Cultural Affairs and Special Events\, Forvis Mazars\, FS Foundation\, Fu
 nFund\, The Illinois Arts Council\, The National Endowment for the Arts\, 
 The Paul M. Angell Family Foundation\, Rusin Law\, The Saints and generous
  individuals like you!
LOCATION:The Edge Theater
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=
 5#/details/ablefest-celebrating-10-years-of-artists-breaking-limits-expect
 ations/18339368/2026-05-02T14
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
