BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Newberry Consort Presents: Revolution! Early American Music
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260507T193000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260507T193000
UID:260327m6X2Uujl1EaoxUcnWfKEvg
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/hOBazxqUd0ettXAh22HMPw.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Revolution! Early American Music from the Signing of the Decla
 ration of Independence to the Civil War\n\nAs the United States reaches it
 s 250th anniversary\, The Newberry Consort performs a program of music tha
 t shaped the founding of our nation. Using early American instruments such
  as the square piano\, keyed bugle\, fiddle\, percussion\, as well as an e
 nsemble of vocal specialists\, this concert connects America’s musical p
 ast and present through early American styles and composers. The program a
 lso features a world premiere of an original composition for American peri
 od instruments and voices written by composer and bass-baritone Jonathan W
 oody.\n\nThursday\, May 7 at 7:30 p.m. at First Presbyterian Church\, 1427
  Chicago Ave.\, Evanston\n\nFriday\, May 8 at 7:30 p.m. First Unitarian Ch
 urch of Chicago\, 5650 S. Woodlawn Ave.\, Chicago\n\nSaturday\, May 9 at 5
  p.m.\, Saint Joseph Chapel\, 1515 S Layton Blvd\, Milwaukee\n\nSunday\, M
 ay 10 at 4 p.m. Ganz Hall\, Roosevelt University\, 430 S. Michigan Ave.\, 
 Chicago\n\nVIRTUAL BROADCAST: Streaming online June 1-22\, 2026\n\nTickets
 : $70 preferred seating\, $45 general admission\, $25 affordable access\, 
 $10 students w/ID\, children under 16 free.\n\nTo purchase tickets please 
 visit www.newberryconsort.org
LOCATION:First Presbyterian Church
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=
 5#/details/the-newberry-consort-presents-revolution-early-american-music/1
 8396680/2026-05-07T19
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Lovestruck Balladeers w. Joel Paterson
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260507T193000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260507T193000
UID:260221WcjhFdzUsESe3H-zP4UWRg
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/Ha0FT2MJjkCBClDt5mPDKQ.large.png
DESCRIPTION:The Lovestruck Balladeers enchant audiences with their masterf
 ul performances and inspired repertoire of ragtime\, jazz and beautiful so
 ngs from around the world. Born out of New Yorks vibrant classic jazz and 
 traditional music scene\, The Lovestruck Balladeers formed during a series
  of recording sessions for Jalopy Records 2018 release\, Estrellas de Radi
 o. Since their debut at The Brooklyn Folk Festival that same year\, the ve
 rsatile quintet has made a name for itself as a compelling act highlightin
 g musical excellence\, fresh arrangements\, original songs and a tightly c
 rafted stage show. The Lovestruck Balladeers are Jake Sanders\, Dennis Lic
 htman\, Sean Cronin\, Dalton Ridenhour and Mike Davis
LOCATION:Evanston SPACE
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=
 5#/details/the-lovestruck-balladeers-w-joel-paterson/18170710/2026-05-07T1
 9
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
