 ortalimages/portalimages/bt8Q0vom1EuQf8sI-oM16Q.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Award-winning Redtwist Theatre announces the cast and creative
  team for ‘night Mother\, April 16 - May 24\, by Marsha Norman and direc
 ted by Executive Artistic Director Dusty Brown\, at Redtwist Theatre\, 104
 4 W. Bryn Mawr Ave.\n\nLife has been difficult for Jessie and her hope for
  the future has faded. Spiraling between a failed marriage and caretaker f
 atigue due to her criminal son and aging mother\, Jessie is determined to 
 take control of her life in the only way left to her. When society and tec
 hnology isolate Jessie\, when the world turns to chaos around her and a pr
 omised future fades away: Jessie digs up her father’s old pistol with th
 e intention to end her life. Marsha Norman’s Pulitzer Prize-winning play
  launches audiences through a mother and daughter’s darkest night togeth
 er.\n\n The ‘night Mother cast includes Anne Sheridan Smith and Kathy R
 uhl. The performance schedule is Thursdays - Saturdays at 7:30 p.m. and Su
 ndays at 3:30 p.m. with a total running time of 90 minutes with no intermi
 ssion. There will be two understudy performances on Sunday\, May 3 at 3:30
  p.m. and Thursday\, May 14 at 7:30 p.m. Single tickets are now on sale fo
 r $10 - $60 at RedtwistTheatre.org with discounts available for seniors\, 
 students and veterans with pay-what-you-can for all Friday night performan
 ces.
LOCATION:Redtwist Theatre
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=
 5#/details/redtwist-theatre-s-night-mother-by-marsha-norman/18381679/2026-
 05-07T19
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
