UID:251230kB6sjtE1G0ajXcUusCNxBA
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/9OiQXPdMBUOTtq6pASq93g.large.png
DESCRIPTION:Founded and led by pianist and composer Renee Rosnes\, ARTEMIS
  is a powerful ensemble of instrumental virtuosos. Along with Rosnes\, the
  quintet consists of trumpeter Ingrid Jensen\, saxophonist Nicole Glover\,
  bassist Noriko Ueda and drummer Allison Miller.After experiencing an ARTE
 MIS live show at the 2018 Newport Jazz Festival\, Blue Note Records Presid
 ent\, Don Was\, signed the band to the label. Their third recording Arbore
 sque will be released February 28\, 2025. The album is testament to the gr
 oups evolving musical landscape featuring stellar arrangements and rivetin
 g originals contributed by all members of the band.Performances across Nor
 th America and Europe at major venues and festivals have garnered high pra
 ise from audiences and critics alike. NPR hailed the band as a killer line
 -up of players\, composers and performerswho converge on an extremely cosm
 opolitan\, sleek\, rhythm-forward\, modern sound. It is no wonder that ART
 EMIS has been awarded \\#1 Group of the Year in the Annual Downbeat Reader
 s Poll for three consecutive years: 2023\, 2024 and 2025!ARTEMIS gave one 
 of the best Keystone Korner performances of all time.Todd Barkan NEA Jazz 
 Master Keystone Korner Baltimore
LOCATION:Evanston SPACE
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=
 5#/details/artemis-early-presented-by-wdcb/17655909/2026-05-10T19
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
