BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Redtwist Theatre's "‘Night Mother" By Marsha Norman
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260521T193000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260521T193000
UID:260325oQO902Wl-0eTc8JqoY92bw
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/bt8Q0vom1EuQf8sI-oM16Q.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:Award-winning Redtwist Theatre announces the cast and creative
  team for ‘night Mother\, April 16 - May 24\, by Marsha Norman and direc
 ted by Executive Artistic Director Dusty Brown\, at Redtwist Theatre\, 104
 4 W. Bryn Mawr Ave.\n\nLife has been difficult for Jessie and her hope for
  the future has faded. Spiraling between a failed marriage and caretaker f
 atigue due to her criminal son and aging mother\, Jessie is determined to 
 take control of her life in the only way left to her. When society and tec
 hnology isolate Jessie\, when the world turns to chaos around her and a pr
 omised future fades away: Jessie digs up her father’s old pistol with th
 e intention to end her life. Marsha Norman’s Pulitzer Prize-winning play
  launches audiences through a mother and daughter’s darkest night togeth
 er.\n\n The ‘night Mother cast includes Anne Sheridan Smith and Kathy R
 uhl. The performance schedule is Thursdays - Saturdays at 7:30 p.m. and Su
 ndays at 3:30 p.m. with a total running time of 90 minutes with no intermi
 ssion. There will be two understudy performances on Sunday\, May 3 at 3:30
  p.m. and Thursday\, May 14 at 7:30 p.m. Single tickets are now on sale fo
 r $10 - $60 at RedtwistTheatre.org with discounts available for seniors\, 
 students and veterans with pay-what-you-can for all Friday night performan
 ces.
LOCATION:Redtwist Theatre
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=
 5#/details/redtwist-theatre-s-night-mother-by-marsha-norman/18381679/2026-
 05-21T19
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:[producing body] Presents "Spaceman"\, May 19 - June 13 at Edge Of
 f-Broadway
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260521T193000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260521T193000
UID:260313O5hN-pBkZU-6Rq-gwt9AkQ
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/vgFRD28Z302jfStfDa5DEw.large.jpg
DESCRIPTION:\\[producingbody\\] is pleased to announce the Chicago premier
 e of Spaceman\, by Leegrid Stevens and directed by Eric Slater\, May 19 - 
 June 13\, at The Edge Off-Broadway\, 1133 W. Catalpa Ave. \n\n In Spacem
 an\, the difficulties of interplanetary space travel are explored in exact
 ing detail throughout this one-woman\, sci-fi odyssey. Radiation exposure\
 , long term weightlessness\, low light\, extensive communication delays an
 d poor hygiene are just a few of the challenges astronaut Molly Jennis mus
 t face as the first human to visit Mars. But she soon finds nothing compar
 es to the psychological effects of having so much time alone. Time spent m
 ulling over the decisions she has made and what might be waiting for her w
 hen she finally reaches her destination.\n\nThe cast of Spaceman includes 
 Ashley Neal \\(she/her\, Molly Jennis\\)\; Allyce Torres \\(she/her\, ense
 mble puppeteer/Ares\\) and Amy Carpenter \\(she/her\, Molly Jennis U/S\\).
 \n\nThe production team includes Leegrid Stevens \\(he/him\, playwright\\)
 \; Eric Slater \\(he/him\, director\\)\; Amy Carpenter \\(she/her\, execut
 ive producer\\)\; Taylor Dalton \\(she/her\, executive producer/set design
 /costume design\\)\; Angela Joy Baldasare \\(she/her\, sound designer\\) a
 nd Garrett Bell \\(he/him\, lighting designer\\).  \n\nThe Spaceman perf
 ormance schedule is Thursdays and Fridays at 7:30 p.m.\, Saturdays at 4:30
  and 7:30 p.m. and Sundays at 5 p.m. Ticket prices are $15-45. The running
  time is 100 minutes with no intermission. Tickets go on sale Friday\, Apr
 il 3 at 12 p.m. at producingbody.com.
LOCATION:The Edge Off-Broadway
URL:http://producingbody.com
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
