BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Factory Theater's "The Sporting Life"
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260523T200000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260523T223000
UID:260209zfVxX_tHKkqjbuhX59ApFA
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/F-ApAohlckO6BfER6kvGZA.large.png
DESCRIPTION:The Factory Theater\, 1623 W. Howard St.\, presents The Sporti
 ng Life\, October 10 – November 22\, written by Marjorie Muller and dire
 cted by Kayla Menz. \n\n16-year-old Dot still hasn’t gotten her period. 
 Lucky for her\, there’s a Witch in the woods who can get it started. How
 ever\, in exchange\, Dot must offer her the life of a man who has wronged 
 her. And who better to offer than a math teacher? When Dot gets her elusiv
 e first period and becomes witness to the Witch’s murder\, they become b
 onded in literal blood\, sending Dot down a path of self-understanding\, b
 itterness\, and perhaps a little bit of violence too \\(as a treat\\). The
  Sporting Life is a “coming of rage” story brutally snapped open to ex
 pose the\, sometimes literal\, entrails of growing up girl. \n\nThe perfor
 mance schedule is October 10 – November 22  Fridays and Saturdays at 8 
 p.m.\, and Sundays at 3 p.m. There will be two additional Thursday perform
 ances November 13 and 20 at 8 p.m. An accessibility performance will occur
  on Sunday\, Nov. 2. The Tickets are $10 – $30 and may be purchased thro
 ugh the box office by calling 312-275-5757 or by visiting TheFactoryTheate
 r.com.
LOCATION:The Factory Theater
URL:https://evanstonmade.org/event/the-factory-theaters-the-sporting-life/
 2026-05-23/
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:In The TIme of the Butterflies
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260523T000000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260523T000000
UID:2511212rl_k2OJD0Gc1h916yAAHQ
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/xNt9BxaPnk6WGpPsUir_ug.large.png
DESCRIPTION:Known as “The Butterflies\,” the spirited and courageous M
 irabal sisters inspired a fight for freedom in the Dominican Republic. For
  30 years\, President Trujillo's iron fist of authoritarianism tightened a
 round the throat of the Dominican Republic. But the people would not be si
 lenced\, and as the revolution grew\, so too did the four Mirabal sisters.
  As the girls became women\, their deep love for their family and passion 
 for their country led them to become activists and martyrs for the revolut
 ion against the Trujillo dictatorship. Their legacy led to the creation of
  the United Nations International Day for the Elimination of Violence agai
 nst Women. Based on Julia Alvarez' acclaimed novel\, this play bears witne
 ss to the joy and laughter\, terror and violence that shaped a nation and 
 its people. Approximate run time: 2 hours and 15 minutes\, with one interm
 ission. Suggested ages: Intended for Mature Audiences
LOCATION:Wirtz Center for the Performing Arts Josephine Louis Theater
URL:https://www.visitchicagonorthshore.com/events/in-the-time-of-the-butte
 rflies
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Pravda Records Presents: Chris Greene Quartet - CGQ Turns 21
DTSTART;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260524T190000
DTEND;TZID=CDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260524T190000
UID:260228idRdDQV1wUqXuT3xc4XPeA
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://citysparkstorage.blob.core.windows.net/p
 ortalimages/portalimages/wDAISmP1KESY2HT6gejgyg.large.png
DESCRIPTION:Pravda Records Presents: Chris Greene Quartet CGQ Turns 21!Ope
 ning set by DJ Pickled Beets. The Chris Greene Quartet comes of age! Led b
 y native-Evanstonian saxophone giant Chris Greene\, the CGQ has been toget
 her for 21 years. Featuring Damian Espinosa on piano and keyboards\, Marc 
 Piane on acoustic and electric bass\, and drummer Steve Corley\, the bands
  unique chemistry is the result of having this stable lineup for most of t
 hat 21 years. It has been one of the most highly-visible units on Chicagos
  fertile jazz scene\, critically lauded and three-time recipients of the C
 hicago Readers Best of Chicago Readers Poll as Best Jazz Ensemble. The ban
 ds music respects the heritage and history of Jazz\, Americas Black creati
 ve music\, while incorporating elements of funk\, hip-hop\, rock\, Afro-Cu
 ban music\, the blues and reggae\, reflecting the diverse backgrounds of t
 he band-members. The CGQ is currently celebrating the release of Conversan
 ce\, the first-ever jazz album released by Pravda Records\, Chicagos longe
 st-running indie-rock label. Now you can buy them a whiskey! DJ Pickled Be
 ets \\(aka Jenny Greene\\) will spin at doors and after the concert.
LOCATION:Evanston SPACE
URL:https://cityspark.com/calendar/#!/show?location=Evanston,+IL&distance=
 5#/details/pravda-records-presents-chris-greene-quartet-cgq-turns-21/18248
 589/2026-05-24T19
X-SOURCE:CitySpark Evanston
END:VEVENT
